news.title: Delhi metro's blue line extension plan from Noida Electronic City to Sahibabad may be revived
news.para: A revised project report submitted by DMRC in Jan had pegged the project's cost at Rs 1,873 crore, up from the estimated Rs 1,517 crore in a 2018 report. The report suggested that 80% of the project cost, which is Rs 1,225.34 crore, should be borne by the state govt through its agencies. UP will foot another Rs 111.8 crore in state taxes.

news.title: Housing society committee members in Maharashtra can respond to complaints online
news.para: Officials from the state cooperation department have said the portal will be upgraded in Oct to enable this two-way communication from Nov.

news.title: Canada's housing affordability crisis may persist for years despite rate cuts
news.para: Even with expectations that Bank of Canada will keep cutting rates in the coming months, the issue of home affordability - which has strangled Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's poll numbers - is unlikely to fade before the next election.

news.title: Property shares in China surge due to easier home purchase rules
news.para: China's Politburo pledged last week to strive to achieve the 2024 economic growth target of roughly 5% and halt declines in the housing market, two days after the central bank unveiled its biggest stimulus since the pandemic.

news.title: Kerala registers 425 illegal sand mining cases in FY24
news.para: As per govt records, 425 cases were registered in the state for illegal sand mining in 2023-24 financial year. The highest number of cases were registered in Malappuram with 222 cases, followed by Kasaragod with 91 cases, raising concerns about the threat to rivers in these districts.

news.title: NCLAT allows Supertech to resume work on Doon Square in Dehradun
news.para: NCLAT's approval clears the way for completion of Doon Square within 515 days, or just over one year and four months. There are a total of 750 units planned in the project, of which just 150 studio apartments have been handed over. The remaining are pending.

news.title: Basic Home Loan raises Rs 87.5 crore in series-B funding round
news.para: The investment was led by Bertelsmann India Investments (BII), the strategic investment arm of German giant Bertelsmann SE & Co. KGaA, along with CE-Ventures, the venture capital platform of Crescent Enterprises, a leading global, diversified business headquartered in the UAE.

news.title: Hyderabad metro phase II to link airport and 'fourth city'
news.para: "We changed the alignment as there is a lot of activity on the Bengaluru highway. Around 5,000 flats are being constructed in this area," said NVS Reddy, managing director of the Hyderabad Airport Metro Limited (HAML).

news.title: Pune's civil court to Swargate metro line opens for public
news.para: Prime Minister Narendra Modi virtually inaugurated the underground Metro stretch, which included Kasba Peth, Mandai and Swargate stations, via a video link on Sunday.

news.title: UK's Rightmove rejects $8.29 billion proposal from REA Group
news.para: Rightmove said its board, after taking into consideration the views of shareholders and considering representations from REA's chair and management team, had concluded that the proposal put forward on Friday remained "unattractive".

news.title: China to cut existing mortgage rates by October-end to boost property market
news.para: Commercial banks should, in batches, reduce interest rates on existing mortgages to no less than 30 basis points (bps) below the Loan Prime Rate (LPR), the central bank's benchmark rate for mortgages, according to a statement released by the People's Bank of China (PBOC).

news.title: Chennai civic body empanels trucks for clearing construction debris
news.para: The city generates about 850 tonnes of construction waste daily, with illegal dumping rampant. On Saturday, the corporation fined multiple households and trucks of 2.05 lakh for dumping waste in areas — Kodungaiyur, Captain Cotton, and Vyasarpadi canals.

news.title: Delhi development body enhances housing schemes with a fresh finish and green spaces
news.para: "DDA's horticulture department is busy developing greens around the housing pockets to improve the quality of life for buyers. Besides, additional final touches are being given to housing blocks to add value," said an official.

news.title: Indore administration receives 2,444 applications seeking land ownership rights
news.para: The district administration organised camps at tehsil offices in Indore for granting leases, in which around 266 applications were received in Kanadia, 334 in Rau, 687 in Malharganj, 595 in Juni Indore, and 562 in Bhicholi Hapsi.

news.title: Maharashtra CM assures to make Cidco houses freehold in Nashik
news.para: Shinde's assurances came while he was addressing a gathering at a local programme for the Balasaheb Thackeray Smriti Udyan in the Gangapur Road area on Saturday.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC quashes lease cancellation order issued to housing project in SIIDCUL Haridwar
news.para: The petitioner, Delhi Apartments Pvt Ltd (DAPL), was allocated five plots on lease in State Infrastructure & Industrial Development Corporation of Uttarakhand Ltd (SIIDCUL) DAPL has started construction on four plots, while the project on the fifth plot has not yet commenced, the lease of which has been revoked.

news.title: Lavasa creditors set eligibility floor to begin resolution 2.0
news.para: The minutes of the meeting of the committee of creditors (CoC) held on September 17 show that 77% of lenders led by Union Bank of India (UBI) have agreed to a minimum criteria for bidders which is a change from the last time the process ran without any eligible criteria to "maximise participation" of applicants.

news.title: Supertech opposes NBCC’s takeover plan to complete 14,000 flats
news.para: The realtor also criticised NBCC's cost estimate to complete the projects, which is nearly double that of Supertech's. The developer suggested that stakeholders would benefit more if it was allowed to construct one project at a time, like that in the case of Doon Square.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority mandates stamp duty for builder-buyer agreements
news.para: This requirement, already outlined in UP-Rera rules, ensures that buyers have valid proof of their flat registration and corresponding stamp duty payment at the time of booking. This will protect homebuyers from potential complications related to the sale or purchase of flats and plots from developers, officials said.
